PART 5: det(I+2A) = det(J+S) — PERFECT SQUARE THEOREM
========================================================================

I+2A = J+S where J=all-ones, S=skew-adjacency
det(J+S) is ALWAYS a perfect square (HYP-788)
√det is ALWAYS odd

